Argentine Stocks: BBVA Frances, Hipotecario, Macro, Molinos Rio

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-06-02T16:26:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/argentine-stocks-bbva-frances-hipotecario-macro-molinos-rio.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 11:55 a.m. New York time.  The Merval Index fell 1.2 percent to 3,137.25.        BBVA Banco Frances SA (FRAN)  , a unit of  Spain ’s Banco
Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA, declined 4 percent to 12.10 pesos.
The price of Argentine sovereign bonds fell today, which signals
lower value for banks’ fixed-income holdings.  Banco Macro SA (BMA) 
,  Argentina ’s largest lender by market value, dropped
2.1 percent to 13.65 pesos.  Banco Hipotecario SA (BHIP)  
retreated 2.3 percent to 2.10 pesos, its eighth consecutive day
of losses.  Molinos Rio de la Plata (MOLI)  SA, the Argentine food
company and soy processor that gets most of its revenue from
markets outside of Argentina, plunged 4.3 percent to 26.40
pesos. Shares have fallen 9.9 percent in two days. The stock had
become “overvalued,” said Christian Reos, the head
researcher at Allaria Ledesma y Cia. brokerage in  Buenos Aires .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
